name: Rickey Henderson
summary: Rickey Henderson, renowned as the greatest Oakland A's player of all time, passed away at the age of 65. The baseball legend, known for his unmatched speed, set the record as Major League Baseball's all-time stolen bases leader. Henderson's exceptional abilities made him a formidable leadoff hitter throughout his illustrious career. His loss has deeply saddened the baseball community, with many expressing their condolences and recognizing his immense contributions to the sport.

The latest updates indicate that Dell will remain hospitalized overnight while the severity of his injury is further evaluated.

name: Social Security Fairness Act
summary: The Social Security Fairness Act, which aims to eliminate the Windfall Elimination Provision (WEP) and Government Pension Offset (GPO), has passed significant hurdles. After clearing the Senate, it now awaits a vote in the House of Representatives. The Act seeks to provide long-overdue fairness to police officers, firefighters, educators, federal workers, and local government employees who are currently penalized under these provisions. The bill's passage sends the matter to the President's desk for final approval.
